name: Iris-dataset-predict-the-optimum-number-of-clusters-and-represent
description: To predict the optimum number of clusters for the Iris dataset and visualize it, we use the K-means clustering algorithm. The steps involve loading and preprocessing the data, determining the best 'k' using methods like the Elbow Method or Silhouette Score, applying K-means clustering, and finally, visualizing the clusters with different colors .
